<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Geiger: Looting of players killed by monsters, bug or feature?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Min">Min</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:45 p.m. 27/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Geiger: Looting of players killed by monsters, bug or feature?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I have been hearing rumors that Brad commented about how the looting system is going to stay the way it is, would you like to clarify?

<P>And by the way I remember you posted some time ago about how you think the ideal PvP server would be, you said it's race wars. Well right now with this system you won't ever get unity of a race because you don't know if your so-called 'allies' behind you are fighting with you or just waiting for you to die so he can loot that shiny shield of yours. (This happens every day, I've seen people just sitting behind the person getting beat up and not lift a finger so he can loot the corpse)
<P>So either tell us this won't be changed or hurry the hell up and fix the bug please.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
